Text.SourceString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! I couldn't stop thinking about the wedding yesterday. Everything was absolutely perfect.
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! I couldn't stop thinking about the wedding yesterday. Everything was absolutely perfect.

Text.SourceString: Oh, speaking of which, I need to make a quick stop at the inn soon. Gotta return <NPCName>Suki</>'s claw earrings that I borrowed for the wedding yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, speaking of which, I need to make a quick stop at the inn soon. Gotta return <NPCName>Suki</>'s claw earrings that I borrowed for the wedding yesterday.

Text.SourceString: By the way, thank you for helping me set up Stephen's room.//<portrait=normal>That tank was surprisingly heavy, huh? Carrying it down the stairs was quite the adventure, I gotta admit.
Text.LocalizedString: By the way, thank you for helping me set up Stephen's room.//<portrait=normal>That tank was surprisingly heavy, huh? Carrying it down the stairs was quite the adventure, I gotta admit.

Text.SourceString: Babe, I made something special just for you! Ta-da!
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, I made something special just for you! Ta-da!

Text.SourceString: I made you breakfast this morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! I hope you like it.
Text.LocalizedString: I made you breakfast this morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! I hope you like it.

Text.SourceString: Do you have any plans for the day, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have any plans for the day, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: How's your day, <PlayerName>$player</>? Tell me all about it!
Text.LocalizedString: How's your day, <PlayerName>$player</>? Tell me all about it!

Text.SourceString: I saw the cutest bird on my morning walk today...it was right outside our farm.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw the cutest bird on my morning walk today...it was right outside our farm.

Text.SourceString: I cleaned the windows today, can you tell? They're sparkling super bright!
Text.LocalizedString: I cleaned the windows today, can you tell? They're sparkling super bright!

Text.SourceString: I put all the cleaning supplies underneath the sink, okay? They're all in one place now.
Text.LocalizedString: I put all the cleaning supplies underneath the sink, okay? They're all in one place now.

Text.SourceString: Hey, babe, I need to find my green stocking. Do you happen to know where they are?//I wanna wear it.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, babe, I need to find my green stocking. Do you happen to know where they are?//I wanna wear it.

Text.SourceString: I have to admit, seeing you farming just takes my breath away.//It's like you were made to be in the fields, and it's super attractive.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to admit, seeing you farming just takes my breath away.//It's like you were made to be in the fields, and it's super attractive.

Text.SourceString: Wow, babe, you look smoking hot! That outfit is just perfect on you.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow, babe, you look smoking hot! That outfit is just perfect on you.

Text.SourceString: I miss you so much...all I want to do is cuddle up with you.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss you so much...all I want to do is cuddle up with you.

Text.SourceString: I had to give that window in Stephen's room a serious yank yesterday, and now it's stuck. Ugh, gotta figure out how to fix it soon!
Text.LocalizedString: I had to give that window in Stephen's room a serious yank yesterday, and now it's stuck. Ugh, gotta figure out how to fix it soon!

Text.SourceString: Oh, oh, oh! Are we gonna plant some flower on our farm this Summer?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, oh, oh! Are we gonna plant some flower on our farm this Summer?

Text.SourceString: I love it here on our farm. The inn, yeah...it was big, but in a way, it sometimes made me feel a bit crowded.//<portrait=happy>Here, I feel like I can breathe freely.
Text.LocalizedString: I love it here on our farm. The inn, yeah...it was big, but in a way, it sometimes made me feel a bit crowded.//<portrait=happy>Here, I feel like I can breathe freely.

Text.SourceString: I need to get my camera all set for tomorrow, like, big time! I might have to come early to Alun-Alun to capture the preparations.//Oh, gosh, where did I put my charger? Gotta find it ASAP!
Text.LocalizedString: I need to get my camera all set for tomorrow, like, big time! I might have to come early to Alun-Alun to capture the preparations.//Oh, gosh, where did I put my charger? Gotta find it ASAP!

Text.SourceString: Alice borrowed my waterproof bag, and I need to grab it before we head out for the Tree Planting Festival tomorrow.//Should I check the Inn or Starlet Town?
Text.LocalizedString: Alice borrowed my waterproof bag, and I need to grab it before we head out for the Tree Planting Festival tomorrow.//Should I check the Inn or Starlet Town?

Text.SourceString: My camera is fully charged and locked and loaded for the Animal Festival tomorrow! I can't wait to go!//You're coming too, right, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: My camera is fully charged and locked and loaded for the Animal Festival tomorrow! I can't wait to go!//You're coming too, right, babe?

Text.SourceString: I should bring an extra lens for the Beach Cleanup tomorrow.//I've got these epic long-range shots in mind, like capturing the trash pickers with the inn in the background. What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: I should bring an extra lens for the Beach Cleanup tomorrow.//I've got these epic long-range shots in mind, like capturing the trash pickers with the inn in the background. What do you think?

Text.SourceString: Babe, are we ready for the Harvest Festival tomorrow? Should we do the whole harvest show-off thingy? It's gonna be epic!
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, are we ready for the Harvest Festival tomorrow? Should we do the whole harvest show-off thingy? It's gonna be epic!

Text.SourceString: Back when we were at the inn, <NPCName>Eva</> used to help <NPCName>Betty</> make those delicious mooncakes for the Harvest Festival, like, the day before.//<portrait=blushing>And we'd totally get to enjoy the failed batches, and let me tell you, they were sooo good!
Text.LocalizedString: Back when we were at the inn, <NPCName>Eva</> used to help <NPCName>Betty</> make those delicious mooncakes for the Harvest Festival, like, the day before.//<portrait=blushing>And we'd totally get to enjoy the failed batches, and let me tell you, they were sooo good!

Text.SourceString: I'm hyped to see what everyone's wearing at the Spooky Festival tomorrow! It's always so dark there, so I gotta make sure to bring my trusty flash.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm hyped to see what everyone's wearing at the Spooky Festival tomorrow! It's always so dark there, so I gotta make sure to bring my trusty flash.

Text.SourceString: It's always so dark there...I gotta make sure to bring my flash.
Text.LocalizedString: It's always so dark there...I gotta make sure to bring my flash.

Text.SourceString: Eva wanted to throw a simple party for the twins’ birthday tomorrow. I was planning to let them know that you and I already had plans...'cos the thought of two back-to-back parties—New Year's Eve and a birthday party—makes me feel exhausted just thinking about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Eva wanted to throw a simple party for the twins’ birthday tomorrow. I was planning to let them know that you and I already had plans...'cos the thought of two back-to-back parties—New Year's Eve and a birthday party—makes me feel exhausted just thinking about it.

Text.SourceString: But apparently, the twins said no, probably because the New Year's Eve party is just around the corner.
Text.LocalizedString: But apparently, the twins said no, probably because the New Year's Eve party is just around the corner.

Text.SourceString: Oh babe! PlayTem is going to be in early access next Fall! I'm totally hopping on that train.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh babe! PlayTem is going to be in early access next Fall! I'm totally hopping on that train.

Text.SourceString: It's going to be <Italic>sooo</> much fun to join the community, give feedback, and see how the game evolves.//<portrait=surprised>I'M SUPER PUMPED FOR THIS ONE, BABE! AAA!!!
Text.LocalizedString: It's going to be <Italic>sooo</> much fun to join the community, give feedback, and see how the game evolves.//<portrait=surprised>I'M SUPER PUMPED FOR THIS ONE, BABE! AAA!!!

Text.SourceString: Fantasy Quest IX is releasing this Summer. Oh my gosh, I've been waiting for this game forever!//<portrait=normal>Should I preorder the deluxe edition?
Text.LocalizedString: Fantasy Quest IX is releasing this Summer. Oh my gosh, I've been waiting for this game forever!//<portrait=normal>Should I preorder the deluxe edition?

Text.SourceString: They have these cool cosmetics, like super cool wings! Do you think it's worth it?
Text.LocalizedString: They have these cool cosmetics, like super cool wings! Do you think it's worth it?

Text.SourceString: I'm not gonna lie, I'm not too thrilled about Platypus Mayhem. It doesn't seem promising to me, uh...yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not gonna lie, I'm not too thrilled about Platypus Mayhem. It doesn't seem promising to me, uh...yeah.

Text.SourceString: I think I'll play it safe and wait a couple of months before diving in.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I'll play it safe and wait a couple of months before diving in.

Text.SourceString: Fantasy Quest VII Remake has been an absolute blast to play! I've been totally hooked on this game and loving every single moment of it.
Text.LocalizedString: Fantasy Quest VII Remake has been an absolute blast to play! I've been totally hooked on this game and loving every single moment of it.

Text.SourceString: I used to play the original version after school...and let me just say, the nostalgia, the upgraded graphics...gameplay, all is just <Italic>perfection</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to play the original version after school...and let me just say, the nostalgia, the upgraded graphics...gameplay, all is just <Italic>perfection</>.

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you about Countenance! This game has been in early access for ages, but, uh...you know what?//The developers keep giving consistent updates, so it's like, whatever.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you about Countenance! This game has been in early access for ages, but, uh...you know what?//The developers keep giving consistent updates, so it's like, whatever.

Text.SourceString: It took me a <Italic>million</> years to get past this one chapter with the kid...but babe, OMG, it's one of my favorite horror games ever.
Text.LocalizedString: It took me a <Italic>million</> years to get past this one chapter with the kid...but babe, OMG, it's one of my favorite horror games ever.

Text.SourceString: I used to blame the inn for hampering my gardening skills, but surprise, surprise, it was actually just me not digging the whole gardening scene, haha! Who knew?
Text.LocalizedString: I used to blame the inn for hampering my gardening skills, but surprise, surprise, it was actually just me not digging the whole gardening scene, haha! Who knew?

Text.SourceString: I like watching you farm, though!
Text.LocalizedString: I like watching you farm, though!

Text.SourceString: Turns out, people can't get enough of countryside snapshots! Beach, farm, you name it...it's the easiest money I've ever made.
Text.LocalizedString: Turns out, people can't get enough of countryside snapshots! Beach, farm, you name it...it's the easiest money I've ever made.

Text.SourceString: I’m a sucker for nature panoramas. There’s always so much to take in! So much to share.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a sucker for nature panoramas. There’s always so much to take in! So much to share.

Text.SourceString: Stephen's pics are a hot commodity! He's a pro, always ready for his close-up!
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen's pics are a hot commodity! He's a pro, always ready for his close-up!

Text.SourceString: I get bored quickly. I play video games when I’m tired of editing pictures.//<portrait=happy>Then, if I’m still bored, I watch other people playing video games.
Text.LocalizedString: I get bored quickly. I play video games when I’m tired of editing pictures.//<portrait=happy>Then, if I’m still bored, I watch other people playing video games.

Text.SourceString: Don't ask me why. I guess there's just something cool about watching other people game.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't ask me why. I guess there's just something cool about watching other people game.

Text.SourceString: There are a lot of picturesque spots here. Um…
Text.LocalizedString: There are a lot of picturesque spots here. Um…

Text.SourceString: I don't sell as many shots lately. I wonder why...//It's got me a little worried.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't sell as many shots lately. I wonder why...//It's got me a little worried.

Text.SourceString: Thank you, baby... Hopefully, I can shake off imposter syndrome soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you, baby... Hopefully, I can shake off imposter syndrome soon.

Text.SourceString: Thank you, baby. You always know what to say.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you, baby. You always know what to say.

Text.SourceString: I’m secretly relieved when the girls cancel plans. Socializing can be exhausting sometimes.//<portrait=normal> Shh... just between us, alright?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m secretly relieved when the girls cancel plans. Socializing can be exhausting sometimes.//<portrait=normal> Shh... just between us, alright?

Text.SourceString: I scrub the floor with disinfectant. You could eat off it if you wanted to... Just, uh...don’t, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I scrub the floor with disinfectant. You could eat off it if you wanted to... Just, uh...don’t, though.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I'm going overboard with all the scrubbing.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I'm going overboard with all the scrubbing.

Text.SourceString: Chilling out and watching people stream is nice. But being the one doing the streaming?//I don't think that's my jam. It just doesn't tickle my fancy, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: Chilling out and watching people stream is nice. But being the one doing the streaming?//I don't think that's my jam. It just doesn't tickle my fancy, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: Pizza? Oh yeah. I love it!//<portrait=normal>It’s delicious. You can have cheese, vegetables… Mmm! Yummy.
Text.LocalizedString: Pizza? Oh yeah. I love it!//<portrait=normal>It’s delicious. You can have cheese, vegetables… Mmm! Yummy.

Text.SourceString: The girls at the inn used to organize get-togethers where we would have dinner, watch TV, and sit around a bonfire.//Those little things made me feel right at home.
Text.LocalizedString: The girls at the inn used to organize get-togethers where we would have dinner, watch TV, and sit around a bonfire.//Those little things made me feel right at home.

Text.SourceString: I should pay them a visit...kinda miss <NPCName>Valentina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I should pay them a visit...kinda miss <NPCName>Valentina</>.

Text.SourceString: Are you going to the beach or heading back home, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you going to the beach or heading back home, babe?

Text.SourceString: Not a whole lot going on here. Just working on stacking my portfolio.//<portrait=normal>I'll be home before dinner, sound good?
Text.LocalizedString: Not a whole lot going on here. Just working on stacking my portfolio.//<portrait=normal>I'll be home before dinner, sound good?

Text.SourceString: Yeesh, it's like Mosquito-Mania here! Feels like the heat just supercharges them.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeesh, it's like Mosquito-Mania here! Feels like the heat just supercharges them.

Text.SourceString: It also makes me crave fruit tarts. Hmm...//The heat, not the mosquito bit.
Text.LocalizedString: It also makes me crave fruit tarts. Hmm...//The heat, not the mosquito bit.

Text.SourceString: Oh my, the Spring colors here are just drop-dead stunning. It’s time to farm killer photos. He he!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my, the Spring colors here are just drop-dead stunning. It’s time to farm killer photos. He he!

Text.SourceString: My favorite place to take Spring pics is by the lake. You wouldn't believe how unreal the old temple looks with all those cherry blossoms around it!
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite place to take Spring pics is by the lake. You wouldn't believe how unreal the old temple looks with all those cherry blossoms around it!

Text.SourceString: Wowza, Spring's already here!//I’m excited to take Stephen out again and show him around.
Text.LocalizedString: Wowza, Spring's already here!//I’m excited to take Stephen out again and show him around.

Text.SourceString: I like to take photos of the leaves as they grow. It's like capturing poetry in motion, don't you think? It really captures the whole "life cycle" thing.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to take photos of the leaves as they grow. It's like capturing poetry in motion, don't you think? It really captures the whole "life cycle" thing.

Text.SourceString: Mr. Mayor's put me in charge of all the picture-snapping at the festivals! Pays pretty well too.//What's up next? The Cherry Blossom Festival on the 10th! How cool is that?!
Text.LocalizedString: Mr. Mayor's put me in charge of all the picture-snapping at the festivals! Pays pretty well too.//What's up next? The Cherry Blossom Festival on the 10th! How cool is that?!

Text.SourceString: Babe, babe...BABE! There’s a new Resident Vile game coming out this Summer.//<portrait=normal>Not sure if I'll get it, though. My schedule's pretty packed. I think I’ll just watch someone stream it or something.
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, babe...BABE! There’s a new Resident Vile game coming out this Summer.//<portrait=normal>Not sure if I'll get it, though. My schedule's pretty packed. I think I’ll just watch someone stream it or something.

Text.SourceString: Besides, I don’t think it’ll be on consoles yet.//My laptop isn’t powerful enough to run it smoothly. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, I don’t think it’ll be on consoles yet.//My laptop isn’t powerful enough to run it smoothly. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: Summer snapshots of Coral Island are just the bomb! I mean, come on, who wouldn't wanna see a beautiful island in full Summer bloom, right?//<portrait=blushing>It’s all about those vibrant Summer vibes!
Text.LocalizedString: Summer snapshots of Coral Island are just the bomb! I mean, come on, who wouldn't wanna see a beautiful island in full Summer bloom, right?//<portrait=blushing>It’s all about those vibrant Summer vibes!

Text.SourceString: Living this close to the beach is like having my cake and eating it too.//I can take our little guy Stephen out for a beach day whenever I feel like it.
Text.LocalizedString: Living this close to the beach is like having my cake and eating it too.//I can take our little guy Stephen out for a beach day whenever I feel like it.

Text.SourceString: And let me tell you, the sunrise and sunset pictures? They never stop!//I mean, I could be out there every day, if I wasn't so busy <Italic>not</> doing that.
Text.LocalizedString: And let me tell you, the sunrise and sunset pictures? They never stop!//I mean, I could be out there every day, if I wasn't so busy <Italic>not</> doing that.

Text.SourceString: Stephen is our little ray of sunshine. Isn't he, babe?! Well, he just can't get enough of the beach.//He's practically bouncing with joy inside his tank, every time we go for a walk there.
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen is our little ray of sunshine. Isn't he, babe?! Well, he just can't get enough of the beach.//He's practically bouncing with joy inside his tank, every time we go for a walk there.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I gotta wear my boots. Sure, it's a bit hot, but they keep me from tripping and dropping the camera. Safety first!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I gotta wear my boots. Sure, it's a bit hot, but they keep me from tripping and dropping the camera. Safety first!

Text.SourceString: Yeesh! I wish it wasn't so sticky-outside.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeesh! I wish it wasn't so sticky-outside.

Text.SourceString: I know you can make fruit tarts whenever, but it always feels like a Summer dish to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I know you can make fruit tarts whenever, but it always feels like a Summer dish to me.

Text.SourceString: I <Italic>love</> taking beach photos in Summer. Maybe it's basic, but who cares?
Text.LocalizedString: I <Italic>love</> taking beach photos in Summer. Maybe it's basic, but who cares?

Text.SourceString: Wowza, it’s Summer already! Time for the community beach cleanup. I’m mulling over whether to take Stephen along.//He’d be good company.
Text.LocalizedString: Wowza, it’s Summer already! Time for the community beach cleanup. I’m mulling over whether to take Stephen along.//He’d be good company.

Text.SourceString: Would it be okay if I take photos of you during the Beach Cleanup Festival?//<portrait=blushing>You're gonna look <Italic>sooo</> cute cleaning up the beach! I gotta capture that!
Text.LocalizedString: Would it be okay if I take photos of you during the Beach Cleanup Festival?//<portrait=blushing>You're gonna look <Italic>sooo</> cute cleaning up the beach! I gotta capture that!

Text.SourceString: Pizza is food for all seasons.//Chilly Winter night? Awesome! Scorching Summer day like today? Even better!
Text.LocalizedString: Pizza is food for all seasons.//Chilly Winter night? Awesome! Scorching Summer day like today? Even better!

Text.SourceString: Fall is just... WOWZA! It's beautiful no matter where you are!//But here on Coral Island? Fall here's like the king of all Falls!
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is just... WOWZA! It's beautiful no matter where you are!//But here on Coral Island? Fall here's like the king of all Falls!

Text.SourceString: Taking photos in Fall can be a bit tricky. The composition has to be just right or it's just...blah. But when it works, it's magic!
Text.LocalizedString: Taking photos in Fall can be a bit tricky. The composition has to be just right or it's just...blah. But when it works, it's magic!

Text.SourceString: I don’t really have a fave season. Coral Island is stunning all year round, which is why I just had to move here.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really have a fave season. Coral Island is stunning all year round, which is why I just had to move here.

Text.SourceString: The Harvest Festival is just packed with fun! And the photo ops? Don’t even get me started!
Text.LocalizedString: The Harvest Festival is just packed with fun! And the photo ops? Don’t even get me started!

Text.SourceString: I like taking photos of Stephen in Fall. His blue shell stands out beautifully in the Fall colors.
Text.LocalizedString: I like taking photos of Stephen in Fall. His blue shell stands out beautifully in the Fall colors.

Text.SourceString: Wowza, it’s Fall already! The island is going to look so pretty with the orange leaves.
Text.LocalizedString: Wowza, it’s Fall already! The island is going to look so pretty with the orange leaves.

Text.SourceString: I can’t take Stephen for walks in Winter. It’s kind of sad, but he doesn’t like the cold.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t take Stephen for walks in Winter. It’s kind of sad, but he doesn’t like the cold.

Text.SourceString: I keep Stephen's tank toasty in Winter. He's a real party animal when the water's warm.//The tank thermometer is super helpful. Totally worth every penny.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep Stephen's tank toasty in Winter. He's a real party animal when the water's warm.//The tank thermometer is super helpful. Totally worth every penny.

Text.SourceString: Coral Island is always beautiful, no matter the season.//<portrait=blushing>When Winter wraps everything in a snow blanket, it's like stepping into a peaceful, enchanting dreamland.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island is always beautiful, no matter the season.//<portrait=blushing>When Winter wraps everything in a snow blanket, it's like stepping into a peaceful, enchanting dreamland.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I worry something’s wrong with Stephen, but then I remember it’s Winter, and he’s just going to be less active than usual.//Do you think I should have <NPCName>Yuri</> check him out? Can she even?
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I worry something’s wrong with Stephen, but then I remember it’s Winter, and he’s just going to be less active than usual.//Do you think I should have <NPCName>Yuri</> check him out? Can she even?

Text.SourceString: Sure, it's chilly, but I'm a shorts girl through and through.//I move easier in them. Less restricting.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, it's chilly, but I'm a shorts girl through and through.//I move easier in them. Less restricting.

Text.SourceString: Oh wow, it’s Winter already! No wonder Stephen looks a bit lethargic.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh wow, it’s Winter already! No wonder Stephen looks a bit lethargic.

Text.SourceString: Every time I take a photo of the island in Winter, I think “Winter wonderland.” It really is a wonder!
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I take a photo of the island in Winter, I think “Winter wonderland.” It really is a wonder!

Text.SourceString: I don’t get too stressed, thankfully. It's one of the job perks.//I’m always surrounded by nature and pretty things. It puts me in a good mood, always.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t get too stressed, thankfully. It's one of the job perks.//I’m always surrounded by nature and pretty things. It puts me in a good mood, always.

Text.SourceString: I’m starting to feel the heat... And mosquito bites.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m starting to feel the heat... And mosquito bites.

Text.SourceString: Parting with Stephen that day at the beach was heart-wrenching...but I knew it was time to release him back to his world.
Text.LocalizedString: Parting with Stephen that day at the beach was heart-wrenching...but I knew it was time to release him back to his world.

Text.SourceString: But then, when he chose to stay! My heart swelled...everything just fell into place again.//<portrait=blushing>Thanks for being there for me, baby.
Text.LocalizedString: But then, when he chose to stay! My heart swelled...everything just fell into place again.//<portrait=blushing>Thanks for being there for me, baby.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to take it easy today. I’m still so tired from the beach cleanup.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to take it easy today. I’m still so tired from the beach cleanup.

Text.SourceString: We don’t have anything going on until the third week of Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t have anything going on until the third week of Fall.

Text.SourceString: Um, the Harvest Festival on the 15th is the next one.
Text.LocalizedString: Um, the Harvest Festival on the 15th is the next one.

Text.SourceString: Can you believe it’s the 11th already? Winter is literally right around the corner.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe it’s the 11th already? Winter is literally right around the corner.

Text.SourceString: Yikes. I need to find my coat. It snows pretty hard here.
Text.LocalizedString: Yikes. I need to find my coat. It snows pretty hard here.

Text.SourceString: If my mom found out I was wearing shorts on a windy day like this, I’d be in deep trouble. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: If my mom found out I was wearing shorts on a windy day like this, I’d be in deep trouble. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: Anything cool going on today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Anything cool going on today, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Get it? ’Cause it’s Winter… Cool…//<portrait=blushing>Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: Get it? ’Cause it’s Winter… Cool…//<portrait=blushing>Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: A lot of cool things happen here in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: A lot of cool things happen here in Winter.

Text.SourceString: The Winter Fair is one of them, happening on the 21st.//<portrait=surprised>Wait, it's the 20th, my bad. The anticipation is getting to me!
Text.LocalizedString: The Winter Fair is one of them, happening on the 21st.//<portrait=surprised>Wait, it's the 20th, my bad. The anticipation is getting to me!

Text.SourceString: Eva wanted to throw a simple party for the twins’ birthday tomorrow. I was planning to let them know that you and I already had plans...'cos the thought of two back-to-back parties—New Year's Eve and a birthday party—makes me feel exhausted just thinking about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Eva wanted to throw a simple party for the twins’ birthday tomorrow. I was planning to let them know that you and I already had plans...'cos the thought of two back-to-back parties—New Year's Eve and a birthday party—makes me feel exhausted just thinking about it.

Text.SourceString: But apparently, the twins said no, probably because the New Year's Eve party is just around the corner.
Text.LocalizedString: But apparently, the twins said no, probably because the New Year's Eve party is just around the corner.

Text.SourceString: I gotta book a slot with <NPCName>Erika</> for a quick trim.//Nope, not <NPCName>Emily</>...<NPCName>Erika</> is better at curly hair.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta book a slot with <NPCName>Erika</> for a quick trim.//Nope, not <NPCName>Emily</>...<NPCName>Erika</> is better at curly hair.

Text.SourceString: Could you remind me later, babe? If I don't make this appointment by today, it'll just slip my mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Could you remind me later, babe? If I don't make this appointment by today, it'll just slip my mind.

Text.SourceString: I'll let the rain mellow out a bit, then unleash my camera.//It looks quite muddy out there. I don’t wanna slip and fall.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll let the rain mellow out a bit, then unleash my camera.//It looks quite muddy out there. I don’t wanna slip and fall.

Text.SourceString: Or, you know, we can just stay in for the day...cuddle...watch TV. Yeah, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Or, you know, we can just stay in for the day...cuddle...watch TV. Yeah, babe?

Text.SourceString: I'll let the snow mellow out a bit, then unleash my camera.//It looks quite cold out there.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll let the snow mellow out a bit, then unleash my camera.//It looks quite cold out there.

Text.SourceString: Or, you know, we can just stay in for the day...cuddle...watch TV. Yeah, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Or, you know, we can just stay in for the day...cuddle...watch TV. Yeah, babe?

Text.SourceString: Hmm, what should we have for dinner?//I'm down with whatever. But, uh...anything without pickles.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, what should we have for dinner?//I'm down with whatever. But, uh...anything without pickles.

Text.SourceString: Hmm, what should we have for dinner?//I'm down with whatever. But, uh...anything without pickles.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, what should we have for dinner?//I'm down with whatever. But, uh...anything without pickles.

Text.SourceString: Stephen gets his meals twice a day. I wanna make sure he gets all the nutrients he needs, but I don’t want to overfeed him.
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen gets his meals twice a day. I wanna make sure he gets all the nutrients he needs, but I don’t want to overfeed him.

Text.SourceString: Yikes. It’s storming really hard.
Text.LocalizedString: Yikes. It’s storming really hard.

Text.SourceString: The wind is a bit scary, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: The wind is a bit scary, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: The sand can be scorching on bare feet.
Text.LocalizedString: The sand can be scorching on bare feet.

Text.SourceString: This beach is where I found Stephen. Right over there, in fact!
Text.LocalizedString: This beach is where I found Stephen. Right over there, in fact!

Text.SourceString: I search the beach every so often for injured animals. Thankfully, I haven’t found any besides Stephen so far.
Text.LocalizedString: I search the beach every so often for injured animals. Thankfully, I haven’t found any besides Stephen so far.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Macy</> is having fun.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Macy</> is having fun.]

Text.SourceString: I think I'm gonna call it a day and go home after this.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I'm gonna call it a day and go home after this.

Text.SourceString: Wanna dance?
Text.LocalizedString: Wanna dance?

Text.SourceString: There are plenty of nature and photography books here for inspiration.
Text.LocalizedString: There are plenty of nature and photography books here for inspiration.

Text.SourceString: There’s information about farming and fishing too, isn’t there?
Text.LocalizedString: There’s information about farming and fishing too, isn’t there?

Text.SourceString: You can nap here, and as long as you don’t snore, I think you can get away with it.
Text.LocalizedString: You can nap here, and as long as you don’t snore, I think you can get away with it.

Text.SourceString: I thought about becoming a farmer too, but I couldn’t see myself committing to staying in one spot for such a long time.//<portrait=blushing>Look at us now, I'm married to one!
Text.LocalizedString: I thought about becoming a farmer too, but I couldn’t see myself committing to staying in one spot for such a long time.//<portrait=blushing>Look at us now, I'm married to one!

Text.SourceString: Do you feel a gust of wind? It’s making me sleepy.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you feel a gust of wind? It’s making me sleepy.

Text.SourceString: Where’s the wind coming from anyway? Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Where’s the wind coming from anyway? Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Reaching this place feels like a mini workout. It's kinda far from our house.//I thought it'd be closer, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: Reaching this place feels like a mini workout. It's kinda far from our house.//I thought it'd be closer, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: Hold on. I just spotted an <Italic>amazing</> shot!
Text.LocalizedString: Hold on. I just spotted an <Italic>amazing</> shot!

Text.SourceString: Blah. I need more caffeine.
Text.LocalizedString: Blah. I need more caffeine.

Text.SourceString: Being a photographer means I have to be ready to whip out my camera at a moment’s notice.
Text.LocalizedString: Being a photographer means I have to be ready to whip out my camera at a moment’s notice.

Text.SourceString: There’ve been dozens, if not hundreds, of shots that got away. They haunt me, <PlayerName>$player</>. They haunt me.
Text.LocalizedString: There’ve been dozens, if not hundreds, of shots that got away. They haunt me, <PlayerName>$player</>. They haunt me.

Text.SourceString: You know what’s funny? I don’t like raw fruit, but I love, love, love baked fruit.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what’s funny? I don’t like raw fruit, but I love, love, love baked fruit.

Text.SourceString: It’s a sensory thing! I just hate the texture of uncooked fruit, but once you bake it? Hoo!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a sensory thing! I just hate the texture of uncooked fruit, but once you bake it? Hoo!

Text.SourceString: Mmm… I could really go for a snack right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Mmm… I could really go for a snack right now.

Text.SourceString: Most of my work so far has been nature photography, so I’m really good at framing that specific type of shot.
Text.LocalizedString: Most of my work so far has been nature photography, so I’m really good at framing that specific type of shot.

Text.SourceString: I’m wondering if I should expand my work to other things, though.//<portrait=annoyed>What if it gets boring? Buh!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m wondering if I should expand my work to other things, though.//<portrait=annoyed>What if it gets boring? Buh!

Text.SourceString: I had the weirdest dream last night. I was a watermelon, and everyone was standing around me, laughing.
Text.LocalizedString: I had the weirdest dream last night. I was a watermelon, and everyone was standing around me, laughing.

Text.SourceString: I like coming here just to think about things. The ocean clears my head.
Text.LocalizedString: I like coming here just to think about things. The ocean clears my head.

Text.SourceString: Don’tcha just love that sea-salt scent? Ha! That’s fun to say. Sea-salt scent!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’tcha just love that sea-salt scent? Ha! That’s fun to say. Sea-salt scent!

Text.SourceString: I love the dim lights here. I can handle loud noises just fine. It’s my eyes that are too sensitive.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the dim lights here. I can handle loud noises just fine. It’s my eyes that are too sensitive.

Text.SourceString: There are some awesome photography books here. <NPCName>Millie</> got some just for me! She’s a real doll.
Text.LocalizedString: There are some awesome photography books here. <NPCName>Millie</> got some just for me! She’s a real doll.

Text.SourceString: Hmm, which orientation should I choose? Landscape or portrait?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, which orientation should I choose? Landscape or portrait?

Text.SourceString: Hang on, I need to change my lens.
Text.LocalizedString: Hang on, I need to change my lens.

Text.SourceString: The light on the sea is perfect. <PlayerName>$player</>, look at that!
Text.LocalizedString: The light on the sea is perfect. <PlayerName>$player</>, look at that!

Text.SourceString: Buh! The sun is so bright today, it hurts my eyes. But it’s such good lighting for photography.
Text.LocalizedString: Buh! The sun is so bright today, it hurts my eyes. But it’s such good lighting for photography.

Text.SourceString: My head hurts. It’s the light. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: My head hurts. It’s the light. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.

Text.SourceString: It’s so cold out there! I’d bundle up a little more if I were you.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so cold out there! I’d bundle up a little more if I were you.

Text.SourceString: So much snow! Wish I had taller boots. My socks are getting soaked.
Text.LocalizedString: So much snow! Wish I had taller boots. My socks are getting soaked.

Text.SourceString: When it storms, it literally goes all day. How do the clouds not run out of water?
Text.LocalizedString: When it storms, it literally goes all day. How do the clouds not run out of water?

Text.SourceString: I bet I could get some awesome lightning shots if I were patient enough! But I’m tired.
Text.LocalizedString: I bet I could get some awesome lightning shots if I were patient enough! But I’m tired.

Text.SourceString: I went out exploring the other day and found so much fruit on the ground.//I don’t like it, but I didn’t want it to go to waste, so I decided to bring it back home.
Text.LocalizedString: I went out exploring the other day and found so much fruit on the ground.//I don’t like it, but I didn’t want it to go to waste, so I decided to bring it back home.

Text.SourceString: I was totally gonna stash it in the fridge for you, but I stumbled upon some cute monkeys.//So, yeah, I couldn't resist. I ended up giving the fruit to them. Sorry, babe!
Text.LocalizedString: I was totally gonna stash it in the fridge for you, but I stumbled upon some cute monkeys.//So, yeah, I couldn't resist. I ended up giving the fruit to them. Sorry, babe!

Text.SourceString: Have you played Battle Oreon? The graphics are out of this world.//You should see it!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you played Battle Oreon? The graphics are out of this world.//You should see it!

Text.SourceString: We should play.//I’ll heat up some pizza and crack open a bottle of wine. It’ll be so much fun.
Text.LocalizedString: We should play.//I’ll heat up some pizza and crack open a bottle of wine. It’ll be so much fun.

Text.SourceString: I’m working on honing my urban photography skills this Spring.//I mean, as urban as it gets on Coral Island.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m working on honing my urban photography skills this Spring.//I mean, as urban as it gets on Coral Island.

Text.SourceString: I tried wearing sunglasses all the time because harsh light bothers me a lot.//But I can’t take good pictures that way.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried wearing sunglasses all the time because harsh light bothers me a lot.//But I can’t take good pictures that way.

Text.SourceString: I still get grumpy on super sunny days. I promise that’s not your fault! It’s worth it for the pics, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I still get grumpy on super sunny days. I promise that’s not your fault! It’s worth it for the pics, though.

Text.SourceString: Are you hungry? I’m always hungry. I have a snack if you want one!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you hungry? I’m always hungry. I have a snack if you want one!

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.
